caption: Crazy crazy overpriced for old not fresh juice - 12$ is wayy too much- the cold brew blended drink was un-drinkable, like it wasn't blended all the way and made me gag- I took it home and blended it some more in my vitamix and it was actually OK (not good) but if you are going to charge so much it's disappointing how poorly prepared things are. Overall: Clean and kind employees, but a tad bit expensive for size. Good smoothie flavors, but nothing innovative or memorable.  We ordered two Bee Greens and one Dragon Bomb. I asked for one of the Bee Greens to be made without pollen and to be extra blended for my dad who has some trouble swallowing. The did as an asked but unfortunately it wasn't as filled as the other Bee Green. To be honest, they were all filled at varying levels - no consistency. My mom didn't drink hers because she found the drink too tart/sour. My Dragon Bomb was fine. I, however, was NOT asked if I wanted oat or almond milk.  For the price, I expected a slightly larger drink. I don't recall in the board menu or printed them listing the ounces in a drink or bowl.  The restrooms were nice and clean. I appreciate that they separated a restroom for their employees during the COVID pandemic. While I appreciate one of the girls attentiveness to my order request, I found that they weren't as inviting to the business. I did wish to tip them, but I was told tips weren't allowed...so I hope they get decent pay!

Two minutes went by and I got up myself and walked to the sink and only then did the other girl help me with my water. Please note my friend and I were the only customers dining at the counter. Also there was no soap in the bathroom to wash my hands with. These employees are more concerned with carryout orders than they do customers dining in. I asked for a little bit more salad dressing and the rude girl told me $1.00 more. I paid it and it was maybe a tablespoon at the most. Just awful customer service.

And you can't forget about the fact that if you want to do a juice cleanse they offer that as well. It's a very easy way to do it. You even get a nice take-home green lunch box if you do a juice cleanse. They as well have some great little desserts that you can get to go that are vegan. To top it off let's say you don't have your wallet with you you can download the app on your phone you collect points and you can pay with your phone as well.
